      "There isn't much reason to dress up the sector as something it isn't. It doesn't have a landmark mall or a famous market strip the way some newer Gurugram sectors do; its identity is more about being a functional, reasonably quiet part of a very busy city, close enough to the action to matter but removed enough to feel residential. For people living this kind of dual life, always near the noise but choosing to live a bit apart from it, the appeal of a spa that similarly sits a little outside the everyday chaos, on the Delhi side, off NH-48, makes a certain kind of sense.",
      "Add to that the general Gurugram lifestyle, long work hours, a fair share of business travel through the airport, weekend socialising around Sector 29 or MG Road, and gym or yoga routines that many residents already maintain, and the demand for a proper massage or steam session becomes obvious. It's less about having nothing nearby and more about wanting a specific kind of experience, unhurried, well-appointed, and away from the immediate pressures of home and office, that a trip out to Mahipalpur can deliver."
