      "The Delhi Metro's Yellow Line, with its southern end at Millennium City Centre Gurugram, is a citywide anchor that most residents mentally place themselves relative to — not because Sector 8 itself sits on the line, but because it's the fixed point everyone in Gurugram uses to judge how far they are from the Delhi side of the city. Local errands, meanwhile, are more often handled by two-wheeler or car, given how spread out Gurugram's sectors tend to be from each other.",
      "It's a sector where daily life runs on a fairly demanding rhythm — long commutes to Cyber City or Udyog Vihar, back-to-back meetings, traffic on Sohna Road or IFFCO Chowk during rush hour, and weekends that get eaten up by errands rather than rest. That kind of pace tends to build up in the shoulders, neck, and lower back long before anyone gets around to addressing it.",
      "For residents who want something more immersive than a quick chair massage between errands, a proper spa day often means planning a short drive out along NH-48 rather than settling for whatever's nearby. That's the gap a full-service wellness centre near the airport corridor tends to fill — not a substitute for anything within Sector 8 itself, but a deliberate, occasional trip for people who want an experience worth the drive."
