      "For people living or working in and around this sector, daily life usually means some combination of a car commute, long hours at a desk, and frequent trips in and out of the city for work or travel. Gurugram's professional crowd — spread across corporate parks, business hubs like Cyber City and Udyog Vihar, and the retail and office spaces along MG Road and Sohna Road — tends to spend a disproportionate amount of time either driving or sitting, and that shows up physically as stiff shoulders, tension headaches, and general fatigue that don't go away with a weekend of rest.",
