      "Sector 29 sits in the part of Gurugram that residents usually describe as \"lively but liveable\" — a mixed pocket of apartment blocks, independent floors, and a well-known market and entertainment strip that draws crowds from across the city on weekends. It isn't a purely residential sector nor a purely commercial one; it functions as something of a social hub, which means the people who actually live and work here are often the ones least able to find quiet time for themselves.",
